nsnational families make it nearly impossible for parents' sacrifices to result in the benefits they expect. Yet, paradoxically, these hardships reinforce family members' commitments to each other. A story both of adversity and the intensity of family ties, Divided by Borders is an engaging and insightful investigation of the ways Mexican families struggle and ultimately persevere in a global economy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aEmigrant remittanceszMexico. 0aHouseholdszMexico. 0aMarital conflictvCase studies. 0aMexicansxFamily relationshipszUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aParent and childvCase studies. 70(DE-601)1044271750(DE-588)4016397-0aFamilie2gnd 70(DE-601)10445833X0(DE-588)4133734-7aFamilienbeziehung2gnd 70(DE-601)1048670940(DE-588)4240086-7aHispanos2gnd 70(DE-601)1056779300(DE-588)4133736-0aFamiliensoziologie2gnd 70(DE-601)1063883040(DE-588)4003920-1aAuswanderung2gnd 70(DE-601)2235419580(DE-588)4439524-3aMexikanischer Einwanderer2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aamerica.  aamerican border.  achildren of migrants.  adiscussion books.  adivided families.  aeconomics.  aemigration immigration.  afamily issues.  afamily ties.  afamily.  aglobal economy.  aimmigrants and immigration.  aimmigration and immigrants.  amexican children.  amexican families.  amexican migrants.  amexicans.  amexico.  amigrant parents.  amigrant workers.  aovercoming adversity.  aparents and children.  aparents sacrifices.  arelocation.  asocial science.  athought provoking.  atransnational families.  aunited states.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026660540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094583840uhttp